The paper deals with algorithm design paradigms and their application to solving a specific problem, which suggests it belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The problem being solved involves partitioning a graph into connected subgraphs, which is a fundamental problem in both Data Structures (cs.DS) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of dynamic programming, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Search and Optimization (cs.SI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
